Autoantibodies (antibodies that react with self antigens) play a major role in a wide range of diseases spanning autoimmunity, cancer, metabolic dysfunction, cardiovascular disease, infectious diseases, and even neurological and neurodegenerative Though autoantibodies are commonly associated with adverse effects, they can also exhibit protective functions that are beneficial to Autoantibodies, like genetic mutations, may explain a significant fraction of the clinical and phenotypic variation seen between Discovery of novel functional autoantibody responses in patients has the potential to provide insight into disease and therapeutic Our Platform Conformational epitopes are the key to discovering functional autoantibody targets Seranova Bio’s REAP platform was developed to detect autoantibodies that recognize “conformational” protein epitopes (i.e., three dimensional epitopes present when a protein is folded into its native state) which are recognized by up % of Our platform includes over extracellular and secreted proteins to comprehensively characterize autoantibody responses in Partnering We are actively seeking partners from academia, biotech or pharma to decarbonize the world – with the power and potential to remove or reduce carbon from sectors like heavy transport, shipping, steel and cement, and reduce the use of natural gas throughout our global gasification process uses a thermal catalytic conversion process optimized with In the gasification island’s chamber, plasma torches generate such high temperatures (3500º-4000º C), that the waste feedstock disintegrates into its molecular compounds, without combustion ash or toxic fly As the gases exit the chamber, the molecules bound into a very high quality biosyngas free of tar, soot and heavy The syngas then goes through a Pressure Swing Absorber system resulting in hydrogen at % purity as required for use in Proton Exchange Membrane fuel cell Our process extracts all carbon from the waste feedstock, removes all particulates and acid gases, and produces no toxins or The end result is high purity hydrogen and a small amount of biogenic carbon dioxide, which is not additive to greenhouse gas SPEG TECHNOLOGY EXPLAINED WHY PLASMA Plasma technology is based on a principle of When energy is applied, matter changes its state: solids become liquids, liquids become With more energy applied, gas becomes ionized and turns into an energy rich plasma state, the fourth state of A plasma torch produces a direct flow of plasma that reaches temperatures between and When that flow comes into contact with solid materials like plastic and metals, it changes important properties of that Using a plasma torch, combined with % oxygen enriched air, our process produces a high quality syngas without any of the toxic byproducts produced by other gasification SGH2 PLASMA TORCH HOW IT COMPARES Ours is greener than green Lawrence Berkeley National Lab has found that for every ton of hydrogen produced, our process displaces to tons of carbon That’s to tons more carbon dioxide avoided than other green hydrogen production processes, which rely on electrolysis from renewable Traditional green hydrogen made from electrolysis is very expensive to produce and requires tremendous amounts of renewable power, which is intermittent, and water, which is a scarce global Unlike other green hydrogen, our greener than green hydrogen does not require a high electrical energy Electrolysis requires KWh to produce 1 kg of hydrogen from 8 gallons of deionized Our facilities generate their own power (1.8 Kwh per Kg of hydrogen) and do not require external power input to convert waste to Blue, gray and brown hydrogen producers either use fossil fuels (natural gas or coal), or low temperature gasification (<2000º C) to produce dirty syngas with low hydrogen and toxic OUR HYDROGEN: MORE CARBON REDUCTIONS, LESS COST Our greener than green hydrogen is 5 to 7 times cheaper than green hydrogen, and cost competitive with the dirtiest Our production costs (based on current US costs) are projected to be US$2 per kg of green Brown hydrogen produced from cheap coal in India costs US$2 per Blue hydrogen — produced from natural gas paired with carbon capture and storage — costs between US$5 to 7 per kg in the US, and $7 to in Europe and Green hydrogen produced through electrolysis using renewable power costs US$10 to per kg, depending on Gray hydrogen produced with cheap, fracked natural gas costs US$2 per kg in the US, while in Europe, Australia and Asia it costs US$5 to 6 per kg due to higher natural gas Traditional green hydrogen (electrolysis) plants are expensive, have limited capacity, and take a long time to build if they are using new renewable sources HMD Labs - News Home News November , HMD Labs announces Skyflow partnership Health Tech and data privacy API company combine expertise to bring privacy, security, and compliance to intelligent medical devices November , (SAN FRANCISCO, CA) -- San HMD Labs, a provider of a complete and fully customizable data platform built to meet the specific needs of intelligent medical device startups, announced today its partnership with Skyflow , the leading customer data privacy The partnership will enhance the ability to provide secure, patient privacy methods in healthcare Through this relationship, HMD Labs will combine its expertise in medical device development with Skyflow’s Healthcare Data Privacy Vault, which securely handles sensitive healthcare data via an “We’re excited to move into this next phase of secure technology for our Data privacy vaults allow health tech companies to seamlessly and securely collect, protect, and share their data, while preserving patients’ privacy and ensuring regulatory compliance,” said Brian Greene, and chief technology “Skyflow has built a zero trust data vault that any health IT company can put into production in a few Development teams can build a Skyflow vault into their apps at the data It’s a perfect match for our ” HMD Labs, the developers of the NeuronSphere™ suite of components, tools and SaaS Services, delivers intelligent medical device startups a comprehensive and data architecture Additionally, the company allows startups to implement and license its platform incrementally, ensuring the cost and complexity of their data environment never outpaces their funding Skyflow’s Healthcare Data Privacy Vault is a zero trust data vault designed specifically for protected health information (PHI). The vault is delivered as a cloud API, allowing healthcare software teams to innovate more rapidly without worrying about patient privacy, data security, HIPAA, or other regulatory Leveraging its unique polymorphic encryption approach, Healthcare Vault s customizable data schema supports the regulated data types specifically identified by the HIPAA law and automatically ensures compliance with HIPAA, GDPR, and emerging “We urgently need more innovations from the health tech industry, but not without patient privacy at its core,” said Anshu Sharma, CEO and at “Our Healthcare Vault with HMD Labs’ suite lets health tech and device developers build, while their data privacy, security, and compliance are We’re looking forward to this ” About HMD Labs HMD Labs offers medical device startups a complete, composable data platform for their HMD Labs also allows startups to progressively deploy and license its flagship solution, NeuronSphere™, in coordination with their successive rounds of About Skyflow Founded in , Skyflow is a data privacy vault for sensitive Our founders wanted to radically transform how businesses handle their users’ financial, healthcare , and other personal data -- the data that powers the digital Inspired by the data vaults that leaders like Apple and Netflix built to handle customer data, our vision was to deliver the same kind of data privacy vault as a simple and elegant API, something any developer could easily build into their application, the same way they use Stripe, Twilio, or Skyflow is based in Palo Alto, California, with offices in Bangalore, For more information, visit http: www.skyflow.com or follow on Twitter and LinkedIn . A hologram of Iset appears on the […] Read More Posts navigation 1 2 → Follow Angelic on Social Media Like on Facebook Follow on Twitter Follow on Instagram Follow on Youtube Join Discord Metaverse Game Studios, © All rights Press Kit   Angelic The Game Subscribe About Angelic combines strategy combat with distinctive and colorful heroes you often see in narrative Angelic has an equal emphasis on storytelling and RPG elements, all backed by a dark and compelling setting in which you are often mesmerized by the complexity of the events happening around Get ready to join a massive conflict, where you will have to question the morality of humanity, and struggle to make the right decision most of the Meet the Crew You are no longer a You have transcended and are now known as Phoenix, a unique You were engineered by Iset the Mother herself, who is a goddess and your redeemer, and also your Zarya Aurora Molnija, your lover, also joins She is an eugenical (genetically crafted super human) Xander, your dear friend, also accompanies you on your He is a war veteran and a former You will meet other companions on your These potential allies might have different agendas, motivations, and You will have to make a team out of a group of people who literally hate each If you can gain their respect and trust, however, you will assemble a fearsome Fight, Kill, Die in an Unforgiving Universe Unlike other games, your companions are not just soldiers with different They are completely different from each They have unique skills, different advantages and disadvantages and they use distinct Units have drop pods, their personal shuttles which provide some combat bonuses as Battles are very dynamic, and controlling a zone is not very easy since enemies can deploy units any place from the sky with drop pods and threaten your formation, even turn the tide of the battle instantly! And one more You might You and your companions are strong, capable, and fearsome, but your team is not Good news is, you are backed by a So even death is not the end of your Captain a Mothership Iset, the very first ever created and practically the mother of many other angels, entrust you captaining her own ship: Osiris is one of a kind mothership with stealth It is your team s You are free to explore the vast universe of Angelic, carefully of course, since the space is full of However, in order to develop your abilities and customize your heroes or craft items and research technologies you will need to salvage parts, help colonies or raid corporations Universe Does NOT Depend On You Angelic is not a game where the entire fate of the universe falls into your Absolutely However, you can still have an impact on many lives: Save them, doom them or ignore Whatever you are planning to do, know that you cannot achieve what you desire all by You will need So, consider your actions There will be Subscribe to receive updates! If not now, when? With everything going on, I think we can all agree that we are living in unprecedented times, and that our society is In particular, issues around Health, the Economy, and Equality have captured our attention like never Current events are already having a profound influence on the decisions we will be making in the next days, months, and It has become evident that we are facing some tough, systemic problems with no easy I want to share my thoughts on these topics, in hopes that we can all aspire to a future that’s better than Over the last two decades, I witnessed the offshoring of manufacturing: the move from developed nations to countries to maximize It was painful to see factories relocate from the West to the East, but over time, I grew to appreciate something unexpected: that manufacturing had served to uplift generations from I thought to myself: manufacturing is an equalizer! We see the rise of protectionism across the It’s early to say if these sentiments are right or wrong, but I do believe that bringing manufacturing back to the United States can heal some of the problems we face To successfully manufacturing and sustain it over an extended period, we will need a new production system built on modern There is an impression that technology increases productivity, but in reality, technology enables people , and people improve The future of manufacturing work should center around the human, and technology should augment the human ability to do Because digital transformation and software will be the foundation for this new production system, US is to lead this Due to the complexity of the current supply chain, companies cannot afford to immediately, and I am not suggesting they I believe a balanced approach where regional manufacturing happens in stages, over time, and based on the value Companies will need to look into their product SKUs, supply chain footprint, digital transformation readiness, and manufacturing technologies to understand what, when, and how to Leaders should have an open mind and leverage global talent to normalize impact and reduce An approach to is : Select high margin, mature, and long products Map the current supply chain and build a strategy, with a local second source where Prepare for digital transformation from shop floor to top Do not and automate at the same Understand and plan for automation automation takes time and Train your current workforce to go digital and energize millennials and gen z to enter Over the next decade, million jobs will be needed in manufacturing, yet million are expected to go unfilled due to the skills Incentives: Leverage local federal government Plan for the A robust, production system has the potential to improve: Health: Our ability to respond quickly to health crises, produce personal protective equipment (PPE) and vaccines for Economy: Job creation bring unemployment down from ~14%. SASE lays out some important principles that allow for a more flexible model to securely connect the modern Gartner predicts that by , at least % of enterprises will have a strategy to adopt â The Ananda Approach to SASE While Gartner has defined some of the principles behind SASE, it did not specify how SASE is to be implemented, and implementations Many SASE solutions today are based on existing centralized products that are put together to check most of the SASE Ananda Networksâ solution introduces a whole new distributed architecture, since a distributed architecture is required to solve the distributed enterprise Our architecture, coupled with our networking and security knowhow, allows us to create the fastest network on the market, and one that goes beyond just the WAN function to provide a unified fabric than can solve virtually any networking use case â whether itâsÂ the WAN, LAN, cloud, or For more information, see our white paper . Artwork Licence Authors HTTPie (pronounced ) is a HTTP Its goal is to make CLI interaction with web services as as HTTPie is designed for testing, debugging, and generally interacting with APIs & HTTP The http & https commands allow for creating and sending arbitrary HTTP They use simple and natural syntax and provide formatted and colorized About this document This documentation is best viewed at docs , where you can select your corresponding HTTPie version as well as run examples directly from the browser using a embedded If you are reading this on GitHub, then this text covers the current development You are invited to submit fixes and improvements to the the docs by editing . Main features Expressive and intuitive syntax Formatted and colorized terminal output JSON support Forms and file uploads HTTPS, proxies, and authentication Arbitrary request data Custom headers Persistent sessions downloads Linux, macOS and Windows support Plugins Documentation Test coverage Installation macOS On macOS, HTTPie can be installed via Homebrew (recommended): $ brew install httpie A MacPorts port is also available: $ port install httpie Linux Most Linux distributions provide a package that can be installed using the system package manager, for example: # Debian, Ubuntu, $ apt install httpie # Fedora $ dnf install httpie # CentOS, RHEL, ... $ yum install httpie # Gentoo $ emerge httpie # Arch Linux $ pacman httpie Windows, A universal installation method (that works on Windows, Mac OS X, Linux, …, and always provides the latest version) is to use pip : # Make sure we have an version of pip and setuptools: $ pip install --upgrade pip setuptools $ pip install --upgrade httpie (If pip installation fails for some reason, you can try easy_install httpie as a ) Python version Python version or greater is Unstable version You can also install the latest unreleased development version directly from the master branch on It is a of a future stable release so the experience might be not as On macOS you can install it with Homebrew: $ brew install httpie --HEAD Otherwise with pip : $ pip install --upgrade https: github.com httpie httpie archive master.tar.gz Verify that now we have the current development version identifier with the suffix, for example: $ http --version # Usage Hello World: $ http https: httpie.org hello Synopsis: $ http [ flags ] [ METHOD ] URL [ ITEM [ ITEM ]] See also http --help . Examples Custom HTTP method , HTTP headers and JSON data: $ http PUT put :123 name = John Submitting forms : $ http POST post hello = World See the request that is being sent using one of the output options : $ http get Build and print a request without sending it using offline mode : $ http --offline post hello = offline Use GitHub API to post a comment on an issue with authentication : $ http USERNAME POST https: api.github.com repos httpie httpie issues 83 comments body = HTTPie is awesome! :heart: Upload a file using redirected input : $ http post < files data.json Download a file and save it via redirected output : $ http image png Download a file wget style: $ http --download image png Use named sessions to make certain aspects of the communication persistent between requests t

The trial, which was conducted jointly at NYU Langone and Baptist Health Jacksonville Orthopaedic Institute and led by Principal Investigator Michael Alaia of NYU Langone, sought to evaluate safety and impact on pain, patient satisfaction and opioid consumption following arthroscopic rotator cuff repair in The findings presented by Alaia at the Annual Meeting of the American Academy of Orthopaedic Surgeons demonstrated that cannabidiol (CBD) administered utilizing the RITe™ Platform effectively reduces pain after shoulder surgery with no safety Highlights of the results include: On the first day after surgery, patients receiving ORAVEXX™ experienced on average % less pain as measured by the Visual Analog Scale (VAS) pain score compared to patients receiving the On both the first and second days after surgery, patients receiving ORAVEXX™ reported % – % greater satisfaction with pain control compared to those receiving Patients receiving mg of CBD reported lower pain and higher satisfaction with pain control compared to patients receiving placebo or mg of The ORAVEXX™ group outperformed the control group at all time No major side effects were “We are grateful for the patients and investigators whose participation in this study evaluating CBD as a pain management therapy may lead to improved treatment options for patients,” said Mark Ridall, Founder and Chief Executive Officer of “We are thrilled with the positive results of this trial, which lays the foundation for several upcoming Phase 2 studies in the treatment of acute and chronic pain utilizing ORAVEXX™.
